The paper proposes a new interpolation method that uses Delaunay neighbors and weights them based on angles formed by Delaunay circles. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves mathematical transformations, which could place it in the dynamical systems (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of natural neighbors and weights also suggests that the paper could be relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and scientific computing (cs.SD).
